counsel for UDAPT (Union of People Affected by Texaco), a group of more than thirty thousand small farmers and indigenous people from the northern Ecuadorian Amazon who continue to fight for reparations and remediation to this day.Eye-opening and galvanizing, Crude brings to light one of the least well-known but most important cases of environmental and racial injustice of our time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aIndians of South AmericazEcuadorzOrientexSocial conditionsvComic books, strips, etc. 0aLiability for oil pollution damageszEcuadorvComic books, strips, etc. 0aOil spillsxEnvironmental aspectszEcuadorzOrientevComic books, strips, etc. 0aPetroleum industry and tradexEnvironmental aspectszEcuadorzOrientevComic books, strips, etc. 0aPetroleum wastexEnvironmental aspectszEcuadorzOrientevComic books, strips, etc. 7aCOMICS & GRAPHIC NOVELS / Nonfiction / General.2bisacsh  aChevron Corporation.  aCristóbal Bonifaz.  aEcuador Supreme Court.  aEcuadorian Amazon.  aLagoAgriooil field.  aPablo Fajardo.  aStevenDonziger.  aUDAPT.  adeforestation.  aenvironmental justice.  aindigenous rights.  alitigation.  aremediation.  asoil contamination.  awater pollution.1 aChute, Hannah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoudeau, Damien, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTardy-Joubert, Sophie, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021 Englishz978311075417908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE